Job Description:
The Company
Rescue provides behavior change marketing services (or "social marketing") to government, non-profit and corporate organizations. Rescue's current work focuses on tobacco, obesity, violence and alcohol prevention; the promotion of exercise, fresh foods and after school programs; and other products and services that promote healthy living. Rescues behavior change campaigns focus on diverse populations within teen (13 - 17), young adult (18 - 26), and adult (18+) populations in both rural and urban areas, resulting in a vast array of campaign styles and strategies.

Rescue is a full-service agency, providing research, strategy, creative, production, web, traditional media, social media, policy change, youth engagement and experiential marketing services to clients in over a dozen states and provinces, as well as to federal government agencies.

We believe that marketing can do more than sell goods, it can create good.

The Job
The Account Development Representative reports to the Group Management Director, Substance Programs, and is responsible for the marketing, lead generation, and pursuit and on-boarding of new business within this business vertical. This includes critically assessing the topic landscape and potential business development opportunities and shaping how Rescue positions itself to competitively win new customers, while adhering strictly to its mission of making healthy behaviors easier and more appealing.

The job of Account Development Representative includes activities pertaining to, but not limited to:

Landscape Assessment & Lead Generation
Forge relationships with key stakeholders to expand Rescues network;
Monitor government funding streams and existing client objectives for priority health topics and assess opportunities to position Rescue to win new work;
Develop database of potential leads and conduct outreach on behalf of Rescue;
Actively promote Rescues work and capabilities to potential clients, including local, state and federal government agencies, community based organizations, coalitions, health systems, and more;
Become topic expert and facilitate outreach calls and presentations with potential partners and clients.
Marketing
Support marketing efforts such as attending or presenting at conferences, pitch decks, writing marketing materials, and more;
Develop new marketing materials to promote Rescue services and products within this vertical;
Execute tactical marketing plans for this vertical developed by partnering internal teams, including but not limited to print, social media, website, or email-based marketing;
Contribute ideas to expand existing marketing efforts to actively grow new business.
Business Development Strategies
Develop an understanding of agency accomplishments and areas of expertise to become an advocate for Rescues mission to make healthier behaviors more appealing;
Assess new business opportunities and identify those most aligned with desired areas of growth, existing expertise, and clients openness to Rescues approaches;
Support business development efforts such as proposal writing and pitch development;
Cultivate new business opportunities for this vertical from existing clientele across Rescue.
New Business On-boarding
Support the transition of pitched work or proposals to internal systems, facilitating a smooth hand-off to the client services team for the new client;
Contribute to the organization of new business or new client information across internal systems;
Equip and empower internal teams to take ownership of and execute new work;
Monitor new business health in partnership with Client Services team
Required Qualifications:
Bachelor's Degree +5 years relevant experience OR 10 years relevant experience OR Master's Degree +3 years relevant experience;
Experience writing new business proposals;
Advanced professional and business writing skills;
Experience navigating public and private sector contracting processes;
Proven ability to network and develop relationships with stakeholders;
Proven ability to work cross-functionally with a variety of teams;
Proven ability to hustle towards tight and competing deadlines; and
Proven ability to present ideas to executive teams and achieve alignment with strategic direction.
Preferred Qualifications:
Non-tobacco use is highly preferred because we only have tobacco-free environments and also to be consistent with our tobacco prevention campaign goals.
Location: Seattle, WA
Status: Full-time
Benefits: Learn more about the benefits of working at Rescue here: http://rescueagency.com/careers/
Travel: Monthly

