The Job

Rescue Agency is seeking a dynamic and high performing Youth Field Organizer to drive implementation of tobacco control and nutrition/obesity prevention policy campaigns across Virginia. We are looking for individuals who are collaborative, open to new challenges, and have a passion for engaging and motivating youth volunteers to lead policy campaign activities in their schools and communities.

As a Youth Field Organizer, youll gain:
Knowledge in key public health issues. Our countrys health is at risk with chronic disease and obesity rates climbing. As a Youth Field Organizer, youll gain access and knowledge of the tobacco control landscape, nutrition initiatives, and the specific policy efforts that can contribute to improved health outcomes.
Community organizing expertise. Your commitment begins with learning Rescues award-winning youth engagement model. You are an expert in field organizing and possess valuable campaign skills. These experiences will help distinguish yourself in a career in community organizing, advocacy, or public policy.
Day-To-Day Activities:


Recruit & Train Youth Volunteers
Recruit and train new and returning youth, including conducting site visits, in-person and virtual training sessions, and coordinating promotional efforts;
Assist the Youth Engagement Manager and program team with developing site visit and training materials, including presentations, activities, and promotional gear.
Track and monitor training participants and new members, including training projects; and
Manage and maintain accurate records and data for program youth members using the MyDot Management system.
Mobilize & Support Youth Volunteers
Recruit and encourage youth members to sign up for campaign projects and events;
Track and monitor youth members Measures of Progress (i.e. surveys and support cards);
Assist youth members with planning, organizing, and implementing successful virtual and in-person events and member meetings, as well as participate in events and meetings to provide technical and on-the-ground support, when needed;
Assist the Youth Engagement Manager with planning and preparing Y Street Leadership Team members for Virginia Healthy Youth Day;
Assist the Youth Engagement Manager with planning, organizing, and implementing the annual Leadership Team Summit, including developing and preparing presentations, activities, and promotional gear;
Maintain frequent contact with youth members to keep them motivated and engaged with the campaigns.
Communication & Relationship-building with Partner Schools Advisors
Conduct web-based on boarding orientations for Partner Schools advisors;
Track Partner Schools progress towards achieving milestone indicators;
Maintain frequent contact with advisors throughout the school year, including sending monthly updates and progress reports;
Help foster and maintain relationships and collaboration between school advisors and youth members.
