Bachelor's Degree OR 5 years of relevant experience;
Experience working with youth;
Excellent interpersonal skills (one-on-one and in a group format) candidates must be able to work successfully within a team;
Excellent team-building, presentation, and facilitation skills;
Commitment to mobilizing youth through strategic organizing;
A desire and ability to motivate youth to take the lead and support youth self-determination while also creating and enforcing systems of accountability;
Ability to multi-task, prioritize assignments, and demonstrate a high degree of initiative;
Flexibility and willingness to shift and pivot in response to the current climate and youth and program needs.
High-level competency with Microsoft Office, G Suite, or equivalent;
Excellent time management skills;
Must be able to work through the entirety of the school year;
Ability to work under pressure and meet urgent deadlines;
Ability and willingness to travel very frequently (up to 60% of the school year) all across the state
Be solutions focused.
Preferred Qualifications:

Experience in community organizing, advocacy, or public policy;
Experience working in school environments; and
